    "narrative": "Today\u2019s optimal lineup for the Zurich Zebras heavily prioritizes stolen base leverage and favorable matchups against back-end rotation arms. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** leads the charge with an elite score of 80.98, primarily driven by an 87% stolen base success probability against the deliberate pace of Merrill Kelly. He is joined at the top of our efficiency rankings by **Junior Caminero** (73.06) and **Trea Turner** (69.28). Both **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** benefit from a plus-matchup against Paddack, whose 4.41 xERA suggests a target-rich environment for our core bats. Meanwhile, **Colt Keith** (65.83) is a high-confidence play; his ability to exploit the slow delivery of Leiter makes him a sneaky threat for a stolen base, an essential factor given our strategic emphasis on the scarcity of that category.\n\nRegarding our tactical decisions, the most difficult bench choice involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, who hovered near our 40-point floor at 42.40 but ultimately lacked the categorical ceiling to displace the current starters. His matchup against Matz was hampered by negative park factors that outweighed his platoon advantage. We also remain cautious with **Yordan Alvarez** (60.46); despite a challenging L/L matchup against Suarez, his elite 0.430 xwOBA keeps him in the lineup, though he represents one of our higher volatility points today. As we monitor the wire, **Christian Yelich** remains shelved on the IL, and we continue to rotate pieces like **Josh Smith** to maintain efficiency. With no major weather concerns currently flagged, our focus remains on capitalizing on the 5.19 xERA presented by Kochanowicz in the **Carson Benge** start, providing a strong anchor for the lower half of our order.",
